{"text": "So, it's time to make a review of this \"great\" game. What we have? Counter-Strike: Global Offensive is a multiplayer computer game developed by Valve and Hidden Path Entertainment. The last major game in the Counter-Strike series of games; like all games in the series, it is dedicated to the confrontation of terrorists and special forces. Counter-Strike: Global Offensive is very similar to Counter-Strike: Source, adjusted for improved graphics and changes in the balance of the game. The economic component plays an important role in the gameplay. Players receive the appropriate cash rewards for winning or losing a round and killing enemy team players. With the money you can buy weapons and equipment. The system of penalties involves a penalty (withdrawal of funds from the virtual account of the player) for the murder of a teammate ($300), as well as a penalty for damage to the hostage (from$ 30 to $1500). My personal opinion: don'T WASTE YOUR NERVES AND MONEY ON THIS PATHETIC TRASH! Why the nerves? Because in almost every rink, or round, you come across cheaters, psychotic small students who damn know all your destiny, or Valve can just throw you out of the game, allegedly errors with servers. In the end, I do not recommend this stupid game! P.S. better go, and buy for this money superb game The Walking Dead: the Game (there about 5 parts of this game) xD", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198356018748", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1531137600.0}
