{"text": "I gotta say if it's action you're looking for, this mod gives it in spades. The island is thick with enemies and yet at the same time it's storyline and plot are paper thin and vague as hell as to why you're even there to begin with. You'll get these weird cryptic messages prattling on about Greek mythology and what to do to further your mission (Something about observing and analysing stuff) and how you're insignificant and worthless (Not sure where they were going with that aspect....) It's challenging and fun but at the same time annoying and vague. Though I did enjoy my time with the mod, I'll say from my perspective the bad outweighs the good. Enemy difficulty is artficially inflated to somewhat ridiculous levels. Just to kill a single combine soldier you'll need to pump about 40-50% of your weapon magazine into them. Found out the magnum got nerfed as I aimed at a combine soldier's head at point blank range and squeezed the trigger. He punched me several times and finally went down after a second shot. It also doesn't help that the A.I's only real strategy is to bum rush the player with overwhelming numbers.  The game really doesn't make it clear at times that you might need to do a little bit of backtracking to find new paths you have opened. Oh and I also forgot to mention this game just LOVES to spawn large hordes of soldiers or monsters behind you. I never once needed to turn down the difficulty but the last part of the game was just one big ol' monster spawn marathon. After I beat the mod it just didn't feel fun to me......almost felt like work. But hey YMMV (your miles may vary)  As always I say give the mod a spin for yourself before you go taking anyone else's word for it.", "appid": "235780", "steamid": "profiles/76561197999406618", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1458648000.0}
